The Belarusian Border Guard Service accused Polish soldiers on Monday of firing at the Peschatka checkpoint with a slingshot. "On the night of April 10-11…the security forces also tried to blind the Belarusian border guards with strobe lights. Illegal actions of the neighboring party were recorded by cameras,"  read a statement from the service. Concurrently, the Polish Border Guard reported on Monday morning that Belarusian soldiers were throwing stones at its members overnight.